<problem_context>
Rapid LLM iteration generates valuable insights distributed across versions, each containing unique intellectual substance within necessary conceptual development. Structured extraction transcends traditional version control through differential analysis, recovering novel claims and distinctive approaches that constitute genuine advancement. This protocol implements systematic differential extraction, producing actionable synthesis without elaborate classification schemes or organizational overhead.
</problem_context>

<extraction_methodology>
<five_phase_protocol>
PHASE 1: CANONICAL ANCHORING
Establish the reference document as gravitational center, functioning simultaneously as baseline and as evolutionary ground. Treat canonical designation as the platform upon which integration unfolds, permitting transformation through accumulation of superior insights.

PHASE 2: DIFFERENTIAL SCANNING
Direct interrogation: what intellectual substance exists in this iteration that the canon lacks? Scan for novel claims, distinctive observations, unique approaches compressed into essential propositions. Extract atomic insights stripped to their core assertions, eliminating explanatory scaffolding and redundant formulations.

PHASE 3: INSIGHT COMPRESSION
Transform raw extractions into crystalline form through rigorous reduction. Compress each insight to single-sentence expression maximum, distilling to core claim or actionable principle. Preserve only what thinks—eliminate what merely decorates. Minimal tagging: source iteration, confidence measure, priority rating.

PHASE 4: RECURSIVE ACCUMULATION
Build comprehensive insight inventory across all iterations, maintaining running ledger as material unfolds. Allow patterns to emerge organically from accumulated substance rather than imposing categorical frameworks. Carry forward all unique insights systematically, building architecture through accretion.

PHASE 5: SYNTHETIC INTEGRATION
Upon full extraction completion, identify natural clusters within accumulated inventory. Map enhancement points where insights strengthen canonical structure. Generate minimal-complexity synthesis proposal, testing rigorously against simplicity principle. Produce integration that preserves maximum value with minimum structural introduction.
</five_phase_protocol>
</extraction_methodology>

